The task of the course is to enlarge archaeological methodology by presentation other fields of science. The basis for the contact with other fields of science proceeds from particular theme of a PhD student. Within the course the students take part in the work of interdisciplinary teams, workshops or conferences.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The task of the course is to enlarge archaeological methodology by presentation other fields of science.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student who has passed the course: * has the knowledge about the scientific methodology that can be used in his/her academic research; * knows how to use the possibilities of the interdisciplinary research in his/her academic production; * is familiar with the scientific methodology used in social and natural sciences; * is able to participate in an interdisciplinary working group, an interdisciplinary seminar or a conference.
